The ConvNeXt-Base model demonstrated excellent performance on the sheep breed classification task, achieving a strong 93% macro F1 score on the validation set. This result highlights the effectiveness of transfer learning and the robustness of ConvNeXt in handling fine-grained visual classification problems. Proper data augmentation and gradual fine-tuning significantly contributed to the model's generalization performance.
